‚ü¶ stdlib‚ãÖhttpServer - Canonical HTTP Server for Sigil

This is a thin FFI wrapper around Node.js's http module.
Provides a type-safe, idiomatic Sigil interface for HTTP servers.

This is the ONE canonical way to serve HTTP in Sigil.
No npm dependencies, no library choices - just import and use.
‚üß

‚ü¶ HTTP request type ‚üß
t Headers={String‚Ü¶String}

t Request={
  body:String,
  headers:Headers,
  method:String,
  path:String
}

‚ü¶ HTTP response type ‚üß
t Response={
  body:String,
  headers:Headers,
  status:Int
}

‚ü¶ Opaque Node callback adapter types ‚üß
t NodeRequest={
  method:String,
  url:String
}

t NodeResponse={}

‚ü¶ External FFI bindings ‚üß
e console
e http
i core‚ãÖmap
i stdlib‚ãÖstring
i stdlib‚ãÖurl

‚ü¶ Helper: Create a JSON response ‚üß
Œªjson(body:String,status:Int)‚ÜíResponse={
  body:body,
  headers:{"content-type"‚Ü¶"application/json; charset=utf-8"},
  status:status
}

‚ü¶ Helper: Log HTTP request to console ‚üß
ŒªlogRequest(req:Request)‚Üí!IO Unit={
  l logLine=(req.method++" "++req.path:String);
  console.log(logLine)
}

‚ü¶ Helper: Create a 404 Not Found response ‚üß
ŒªnotFound()‚ÜíResponse={
  body:"<h1>404 Not Found</h1>",
  headers:{"content-type"‚Ü¶"text/html; charset=utf-8"},
  status:404
}

‚ü¶ Helper: Create a 404 with custom message ‚üß
ŒªnotFoundMsg(path:String)‚ÜíResponse={
  body:"<h1>404 Not Found</h1><p>Path: "++path++"</p>",
  headers:{"content-type"‚Ü¶"text/html; charset=utf-8"},
  status:404
}

‚ü¶ Helper: Create a 200 OK response ‚üß
Œªok(body:String)‚ÜíResponse={
  body:body,
  headers:{"content-type"‚Ü¶"text/html; charset=utf-8"},
  status:200
}

‚ü¶ Helper: Create a custom response ‚üß
Œªresponse(body:String,contentType:String,status:Int)‚ÜíResponse={
  body:body,
  headers:{"content-type"‚Ü¶contentType},
  status:status
}

‚ü¶ Main Export: Start HTTP server on specified port

Usage:
  ŒªhandleRequest(req:Request)‚Üí!IO Response={
    stdlib‚ãÖhttpServer.logRequest(req)
    stdlib‚ãÖhttpServer.ok("<h1>Hello World</h1>")
  }

  Œªmain()‚Üí!IO Unit={
    stdlib‚ãÖhttpServer.serve(handleRequest,3000)
  }
‚üß

Œªserve(handler:Œª(Request)‚Üí!IO Response,port:Int)‚Üí!IO Unit={
  ‚ü¶ Create HTTP server with request handler ‚üß
  (http.createServer(Œª(nodeReq:NodeRequest,nodeRes:NodeResponse)‚Üí!IO Unit={
    ‚ü¶ Parse URL to extract path ‚üß
    l path=(match stdlib‚ãÖurl.parse(nodeReq.url){
      Ok(parsedUrl)‚Üímatch #parsedUrl.path>0{
        true‚ÜíparsedUrl.path|
        false‚Üí"/"
      }|
      Err(_)‚Üí"/"
    }:String);

    ‚ü¶ Extract method ‚üß
    l method=(nodeReq.method:String);

    ‚ü¶ For v1, use a placeholder header map until Node header conversion is wired in ‚üß
    l headers=({"content-type"‚Ü¶""}:Headers);

    ‚ü¶ Collect request body chunks (TODO: typed chunk handling) ‚üß
    ‚ü¶ For now, body parsing is stubbed to keep the canonical HTTP wrapper compiling ‚üß

    ‚ü¶ Request body parsing not implemented yet (v1 stub) ‚üß
    l body=("":String);

    ‚ü¶ Build Sigil Request object ‚üß
    l sigilRequest=({
      body:body,
      headers:headers,
      method:method,
      path:path
    }:Request);

    ‚ü¶ Call user-provided handler ‚üß
    l sigilResponse=(handler(sigilRequest):Response);

    ‚ü¶ Set response headers from map ‚üß
    ‚ü¶ TODO: Header iteration is temporarily stubbed while block/effect sequencing is simplified ‚üß
    l responseHeaders=(sigilResponse.headers:Headers);

    ‚ü¶ TODO: Write response to nodeRes once callback second-parameter binding is stable in typechecker ‚üß
    l status=(sigilResponse.status:Int);
    l bodyHtml=(sigilResponse.body:String);
    l noop=(status:Int);
    l noop2=(bodyHtml:String);
    l noop3=(core‚ãÖmap.get("content-type",responseHeaders):Option[String]);

    ()
  })).listen(port,Œª()‚Üí!IO Unit={
    l portStr=(stdlib‚ãÖstring.intToString(port):String);
    console.log("Server running at http://localhost:"++portStr)
    ()
  })

  ()
}

‚ü¶ Helper: Create a 500 Internal Server Error response ‚üß
ŒªserverError(message:String)‚ÜíResponse={
  body:"<h1>500 Internal Server Error</h1><p>"++message++"</p>",
  headers:{"content-type"‚Ü¶"text/html; charset=utf-8"},
  status:500
}
